message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with music informatics and computational models of perceived musical tension. Other likely sub-categories could be cs.CL (natural language processing) as the paper uses a word2vec-type neural network, cs.LG (machine learning) as the paper involves training a neural network, cs.AI (artificial intelligence) as the paper deals with modelling human perception, and cs.HC (human-computer interaction) as the paper discusses the veridicality of the model's predictions with respect to empirical evidence obtained from human listeners.
